# Run Dev Server When Necessary

Run the development server when it would help the user test or view changes.

## When to run

- After making changes the user might want to test (UI, API, pages)
- When the user asks to run the app or see changes
- When debugging involves the running app

## How to run

1. Before starting: run `npm run dev:kill` first if another instance might be running
2. Use the full path since the project is not in the workspace root:

```bash
cd /Users/larspettersaugen/touring-crew-app && npm run dev
```

3. Run in the background (`is_background: true`) so the terminal stays available for other commands.
